The Butcher's Wife;;1991;;PG-13;;Comedy,Fantasy,Romance;;5.4;;Terry Hughes;;Demi Moore,Jeff Daniels,George Dzundza,Mary Steenburgen,Frances McDormand,Margaret Colin,Max Perlich,Miriam Margolyes,Helen Hanft,Christopher Durang,Luis Avalos,Charles Pierce,Elizabeth Lawrence,Stephanie Laurence,Barry Neikrug,Ed Kenney,Diane Salinger,Cameron Milzer;;A clairvoyant thinks she's met her husband to be because she's seen him in her dreams. They marry quickly, and return to the husband's ("the butcher"), home in the city. She has a big impact on everyone she meets by anticipating their questions and actions and advising them on their love life. Her interference then brings her into contact with the real man of her dreams.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0101523/